results.label: Abdominal Aortic Aneurysm
results.description: Enlargement and ballooning of the vessel that supplies arterial blood to the abdomen, pelvis and legs. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: Abdominal pain
results.description: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen.

results.label: Abnormal circulating lipid concentration
results.description: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation.

results.label: Abnormal EKG
results.description: Abnormal rhythm of the heart.

results.label: Abnormality of skin pigmentation
results.description: An abnormality of the pigmentation of the skin.

results.label: Abnormality of the skeletal system
results.description: An abnormality of the skeletal system.

results.label: ACPA-negative rheumatoid arthritis
results.description: A subtype of rheumatoid arthritis defined by the absence of autoantibodies that are directed against citrullinated peptides and proteins.

results.label: ACPA-positive rheumatoid arthritis
results.description: A subtype of rheumatoid arthritis defined by the presence of autoantibodies that are directed against citrullinated peptides and proteins.

results.label: acute kidney failure
results.description: Sudden and sustained deterioration of the kidney function characterized by decreased glomerular filtration rate, increased serum creatinine or oliguria. [NCIT: C26808]

results.label: acute lymphoblastic leukemia
results.description: Leukemia with an acute onset, characterized by the presence of lymphoblasts in the bone marrow and the peripheral blood. It includes the acute B lymphoblastic leukemia and acute T lymphoblastic leukemia. [NCIT: C3167]

results.label: acute myocardial infarction
results.description: Necrosis of the myocardium, as a result of interruption of the blood supply to the area. It is characterized by a severe and rapid onset of symptoms that may include chest pain, often radiating to the left arm and left side of the neck, dyspnea, sweating, and palpitations. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: addictive behaviour
results.description: The observable, measurable, and often pathological activity of an organism that portrays its inability to overcome a habit resulting in an insatiable craving for a substance or for performing certain acts. The addictive behavior includes the emotional and physical overdependence on the object of habit in increasing amount or frequency.

results.label: adipose amount
results.description: The amount of a adipose tissue. [AUTO: patterns/patterns/entity_attribute]

results.label: age at death
results.description: The age at which death occurs.

results.label: age at diagnosis
results.description: The age, measured from some defined time point e.g. birth at which a subject (e.g. a human patient) is diagnosed with some disease e.g. breast cancer.

results.label: age at first birth measurement
results.description: A measurement of the age at which a woman gave birth to her first live child

results.label: age at first sexual intercourse measurement
results.description: A measurement of the age at which a person has the first sexual intercourse.

results.label: age at initiation of smoking
results.description: Age of initation of the habit of smoking, the inhaling and exhaling of tobacco smoke.

results.label: age at menarche
results.description: The age of onset of (human) menarche, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

results.label: age at menopause
results.description: The age of onset of (human) menopause, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

results.label: age-related hearing impairment
results.description: Bilateral hearing loss caused by progressive degeneration of cochlear structures and central auditory pathways, typically associated with the aging process. [NCIT: C116367]

results.label: age-related macular degeneration
results.description: Age-related loss of vision in the central portion of the retina (macula), secondary to retinal degeneration. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: aging rate
results.description: The rate of the aging process.

results.label: alcohol consumption quality
results.description: The quality of a alcohol consumption. [obo: oba/patterns/entity_attribute_part_of]

results.label: alcohol dependence
results.description: Physical and psychological dependence on alcohol. [NCIT: P378]
trait_synonyms: aerodigestive tract cancer, squamous cell, alcohol-related, protection against

results.label: alcohol dependence measurement
results.description: quantification of some aspect of alcohol dependence or misuse, eg using a cummulative symptom score to determine the severity of a case of alcohol dependence

results.label: alcohol drinking
results.description: Behaviors associated with the ingesting of alcoholic beverages, including social drinking.

results.label: alcoholic liver cirrhosis
results.description: A disorder of the liver characterized by the presence of fibrotic scar tissue instead of healthy liver tissue. This condition is attributed to excessive consumption of alcoholic beverages. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: alkaline phosphatase measurement
results.description: Alkaline phosphatase measurement is a quantification of alkaline phosphatase in blood. AP is a marker for bone and liver disease.

results.label: allergic disease
results.description: An immune response that occurs following re-exposure to an innocuous antigen, and that requires the presence of existing antibodies against that antigen. This response involves the binding of IgE to mast cells, and may worsen with repeated exposures. [NCIT: C114476]
trait_synonyms: allergic form of disease or disorder
allergic form of immune system disease

results.label: allergic rhinitis
results.description: Inflammation of the nasal mucous membranes caused by an IgE-mediated response to external allergens. The inflammation may also involve the mucous membranes of the sinuses, eyes, middle ear, and pharynx. Symptoms include sneezing, nasal congestion, rhinorrhea, and itching. It may lead to fatigue, drowsiness, and malaise thus causing impairment of the quality of life. [NCIT: C79532]

results.label: Alzheimer disease
results.description: A progressive, neurodegenerative disease characterized by loss of function and death of nerve cells in several areas of the brain leading to loss of cognitive function such as memory and language. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: anal polyp
results.description: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic polypoid lesion that arises from the anus. Representative examples include the fibroepithelial polyp and squamous papilloma. [NCIT: C3957]

results.label: anemia
results.description: A reduction in the number of red blood cells, the amount of hemoglobin, and/or the volume of packed red blood cells. Clinically, anemia represents a reduction in the oxygen-transporting capacity of a designated volume of blood, resulting from an imbalance between blood loss (through hemorrhage or hemolysis) and blood production. Signs and symptoms of anemia may include pallor of the skin and mucous membranes, shortness of breath, palpitations of the heart, soft systolic murmurs, lethargy, and fatigability. [NCIT: C2869]

results.label: angina pectoris
results.description: The symptom of paroxysmal pain consequent to MYOCARDIAL ISCHEMIA usually of distinctive character, location and radiation. It is thought to be provoked by a transient stressful situation during which the oxygen requirements of the MYOCARDIUM exceed that supplied by the CORONARY CIRCULATION.

results.label: ankylosing spondylitis
results.description: An autoimmune chronic inflammatory disorder characterized by inflammation in the vertebral joints of the spine and sacroiliac joints. It predominantly affects young males. Patients present with stiffness and pain in the spine. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: anthropometric measurement
results.description: Anthropometry is a measurement of the size, weight, and proportions of the human or other primate body.

results.label: anxiety disorder
results.description: A category of psychiatric disorders which are characterized by anxious feelings or fear often accompanied by physical symptoms associated with anxiety. [NCIT: C2878]

results.label: anxiety measurement
results.description: Quantification of the level of a generalised feeling of anxiety experienced by an individual, typically measured via a questionnaire.

results.label: aortic measurement
results.description: Measurement of some parts of the aorta, including ascending aorta distensibility and area.

results.label: aortic valve disease
results.description: A disease involving the aortic valve.
trait_synonyms: disease or disorder of aortic valve

results.label: APOE carrier status
results.description: quantification of the presence or absence of apolipoprotein E (APOE) in an individual

results.label: apolipoprotein A 1 measurement
results.description: Is a quantification of apolipoprotein A 1 in a sample. It is encoded in humans by the APOA1 gene and is the major protein component of high density lipoprotein (HDL) in plasma. Apolipoprotein A 1 relates to lower observational risk of coronary artery disease.

results.label: apolipoprotein A-IV measurement
results.description: quantification of serum lipoprotein A-IV. Apolipoprotein A-IV, encoded in humans by the APOA4 gene,  a 376-residue mature O-linked glycoprotein.

results.label: apolipoprotein B measurement
results.description: The measurement of ApoB in blood. Apolipoprotein B is a major protein constituent of chylomicrons (apo B-48), LDL (apo B-100) and VLDL (apo B-100). Apo B-100 functions as a recognition signal for the cellular binding and internalization of LDL particles by the apoB/E receptor, and is upregulated in response to enterovirus 71.

results.label: appendectomy
results.description: Procedure to remove the appendix.

results.label: appendicitis
results.description: Acute inflammation of the vermiform appendix. [NCIT: P378]

results.label: arterial stiffness measurement
results.description: An Arterial stiffness measurement is the information output of a non invasive pulse wave velocity assay. Arterial stiffness is a predictor of cardiovascular mortality

results.label: arthritis
results.description: An inflammatory process affecting a joint. Causes include infection, autoimmune processes, degenerative processes, and trauma. Signs and symptoms may include swelling around the affected joint and pain. [NCIT: C2883]
